<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-06-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1440" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1440">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.55/7.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires at
                                Peking</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-06-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your June 19. For some time our Legation has been using its good offices
                            on behalf of the Chinese in Panama. The Department assumes that as the
                            Congress has adjourned until September, 1914, modification of the law is
                            impossible, but will advise the Legation at Panama of the desire of the
                            Chinese Government for suspension of the law pending conclusion of a
                            treaty. If this is not possible the Department will instruct the
                            Legation to use its good offices to obtain regulations not unnecessarily
                            severe.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>